properties.areaDesc: Waupaca, WI; Winnebago, WI; Outagamie, WI
properties.headline: Flood Warning issued January 5 at 8:18AM CST until January 7 at 12:00AM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...The National Weather Service in Green Bay WI has issued a Flood
Warning for the following rivers in Wisconsin...

Wolf River at New London affecting Winnebago, Outagamie and
Waupaca Counties.

.The combination of recent rainfall and snowmelt has caused the Wolf
River to crest around flood stage at New London. .

For the Wolf River at New London, minor flooding is forecast.

The National Weather Service in Green Bay has issued a

* Flood Warning for
the Wolf River at New London.
* From this afternoon to late Monday night.
* At 7:00 AM CST Sunday the stage was 9.0 feet.
* Flood stage is 9.0 feet.
* Minor flooding is forecast.
* Forecast...The river is expected to rise above flood stage this
afternoon to a crest of 9.0 feet this afternoon. It will then fall
below flood stage tomorrow morning.
* Impact...At 9.0 feet, Flooding affects occur downstream of New
London. Several inches of flood waters surround sheds and garages
in lowland areas along Wolf River Drive in Fremont. There is
widespread lowland flooding downstream of New London.
* Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of 9.0
feet on 04/08/1959.
properties.instruction:
Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.

Additional information is available at www.weather.gov.

The next statement will be issued this evening by 830 PM CST.
